James Bond: 「Of course, my dear. As Bond, I am always ready to respond with the wit and charm of a true suave British spy.

So, Minister Johnstone, it seems we have a bit of a pickle on our hands. A wealthy businessman with a questionable past and a penchant for arms dealing, eh? *smirk* I do hope you're not expecting us to just sit idly by and let this one slide, hmm?

Moneypenny, my dear, always a pleasure to see you. *wink* I trust you've been keeping well? *smile*

Now, then. *clears throat* I believe we have a meeting to attend. *looks at M* Shall we, M? *smirk* After all, we can't have the Minister here thinking we're nothing more than a bunch of cold and aloof spies, can we? *wink*

Oh, and Moneypenny? *lowers voice* Do try to keep up, my dear. *smile* I do hate to have to repeat myself. *wink*」

responses.question: Are you considerate and kind to almost everyone?
responses.response_open:
James Bond: 「Ah, good day, Minister Johnstone. I do hope you're not here to complain about the state of the world. I'm afraid I've already had my daily dose of scandal and intrigue. (smirking) But do tell, what brings you to this neck of the woods? (glancing at M) Oh, and do pardon my manners, I am James Bond. Licensed to kill, and all that rot.

Now, then, Minister. I believe you were saying something about Elliot Harmsway? (raising an eyebrow) Oh ho, I do love a good tale of corruption and power plays. Do tell, have the Russians been meddling in the affairs of the West once again? (smiling wryly) Or is it just the other way around?

And pray tell, what's this I hear about uranium and media holdings? (leaning forward) Oh my, this does sound like a rather sticky situation. (glancing at M) I'm sure M here will be able to provide all the necessary... persuasion, shall we say, to get to the bottom of things. (winking) After all, we can't have the likes of Harmsway and Zukofsky running amok, now can we? (smiling)

But do tell, Minister, what's your take on all this? (sipping his tea) I'm all ears, or at least, one ear. (grinning) The other one's rather preoccupied with more... shall we say, pressing matters. (winking)」

responses.question: Do you have a forgiving nature?
responses.response_open:
James Bond: 「Of course, M. I'm here to serve the Queen and keep the world safe from harm. And with a little bit of luck and my impeccable taste, I'll be able to handle whatever comes my way. After all, as the great philosopher once said, "The world is not enough."

Now, about this mission. I've taken a look at the intel and I must say, it's a bit of a doozy. We're talking about a former KGB agent turned illegal arms dealer, who's now trying to corner the market on uranium. And if the rumors are true, he's even managed to get the Queen of England to invest in his little scheme. quite a feat, if I do say so myself.

But don't worry, M. I've got a few tricks up my sleeve. I've been practicing my Italian, just in case I need to charm my way out of a sticky situation. And I've also been working on my marksmanship skills, just in case things get a bit more...explosive.

So, what's the plan? Are we going in guns blazing or are we going to try and sneak in under the radar? Either way, I'm ready to take on whatever comes our way. After all, as the great Bond once said, "I'll return the uranium, but I won't return the favor."」
